-- European stock 'fear gauge' surges to 2-year high
-- By Blaise Robinson
-- Wed Oct 15, 2014 09:52AM EDT
-- None



PARIS, Oct 15 (Reuters) - The Euro STOXX 50 Volatility Index <.V2TX> surged to 28.6 on Wednesday, its highest level since mid-2012 as mounting jitters over the strength of the global economy prompted investors to slash exposure to risky assets.

Europe's widely-used measure of investor risk aversion known as the VSTOXX - which is based on put and call options on Euro STOXX 50 stocks <.STOXX50E> - was trading at around 19 a week ago.